'Yer un dah [stuff and nonsense],' said Krug. 'He will go on licking my hand in the dark. I am invulnerable. Invulnerable — the rumbling sea wave [volna] rolling the rabble of pebbles as it recedes. Nothing can happen to Krug the Rock. The two or three fat nations (the one that is blue on the map and the one that is fallow) from which my Toad craves recognition, loans, and whatever else a bullet-riddled country may want to obtain from a sleek neighbour — these na